thread.title: KeyCorp posts 2Q profit

title: KeyCorp posts 2Q profit
text:
Tip : Use comma (,) to separate multiple quotes. Learn more... 
Thu, Jul 16, 2015, 11:56 BST - UK Markets close in 4 hrs 34 mins KeyCorp posts 2Q profit KeyCorp posts profit of $233 million in 2nd quarter Associated Press – 16 minutes ago 
CLEVELAND (AP) _ KeyCorp (KEY) on Thursday reported second-quarter profit of $233 million. 
The Cleveland-based bank said it had earnings of 27 cents per share. 
The results missed Wall Street expectations. The average estimate of 14 analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for earnings of 28 cents per share. 
The bank holding company posted revenue of $1.07 billion in the period, which topped Street forecasts. Nine analysts surveyed by Zacks expected $1.05 billion. 
KeyCorp shares have increased 10 percent since the beginning of the year, while the Standard & Poor's 500 index has climbed slightly more than 2 percent. The stock has risen slightly more than 6 percent in the last 12 months.
